    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Or is dom.js used in SSR and therefore the browser specific path can't be used.\r\n\r\nWe do not yet have good SSR in react-instantsearch so I bet we could ultimately make this change but it won't be 100% future proof because ultimately we will get server side rendering and the fix will have to be reverted. I'd rather see meteor.js take action or someone (maybe you) do the necessary changes in meteor.js to handle the browser field on packages.",
